<paragraph id="8BD23688A81FFFD1FF5F8D5F67B3FAB4" blockId="2.[136,1452,1055,1406]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81FFFD1FF5F8D5F67D9FAFF" bold="true" box="[189,390,1307,1334]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D0BA81FFFD1FE488D5F64FFFAFF" authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" box="[426,672,1307,1334]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81FFFD1FE488D5F64FFFAFF" box="[426,672,1307,1334]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Lycianthes ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Central and South American shrub or vine with brown, dendritic trichomes, a calyx structure that resembles the closely-related 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D0BA81FFFD1FCBA8D7B66E1FAB7" authority="(Vahl 1797: 20) Bitter (1919: 341)" authorityName="Bitter" authorityPageNumber="341" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="Vahl" baseAuthorityPageNumber="20" baseAuthorityYear="1797" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pauciflora">
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81FFFD1FCBA8D7B620FFA90" box="[856,1104,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Lycianthes pauciflora</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B79A81FFFD1FB838D7B6359FA93" author="Vahl, M." box="[1121,1286,1343,1370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 58" refId="ref7146" refString="Vahl, M. (1797) Descriptiones Plantarum - Praesertim Americae Meridionalis. Eclogae Americanae 1: 1 - 58." type="journal article" year="1797">Vahl 1797: 20</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B79A81FFFD1FAFB8D7B66E1FAB7" author="Bitter, G." pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="292 - 520" refId="ref6023" refString="Bitter, G. (1919) Die Gattung Lycianthes. Abhandlungen Herausgegeban vom Naturwissenschaftlichen Verein zu Bremen 24: 292 - 520." type="journal article" year="1919">Bitter (1919: 341)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and white, entire corollas.
</paragraph>
